\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
Entrants and incumbents can invest in R&D to obtain an innovation reducing
 costs to:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
c_{t+\Delta t}=\frac{c_{t}}{\left(1+\eta\right)\phi},
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pause
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If innovation is 
\emph on
implemented, 
\emph default
cost of all other firms drops to:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
c_{t+\Delta t}=\frac{c_{t}}{\left(1+\eta\right)}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pause
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Normalized incumbents' profits are constant:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\pi_{t}\equiv\frac{\Pi_{t}}{Y_{t}}=\left(\frac{\phi-1}{\phi}\right)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

