\begin_layout Proposition
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "prop: partialEq-2"

\end_inset

 Around and equilibrium with constant growth, an increase in the markup
 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

 raises incumbents' and entrants' research efforts, and the share of R&D
 labor employed by incumbents.
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
pause
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proposition
If (i) inventor supply to the sector is elastic; (ii) 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda=0$
\end_inset

; and (iii) the model parameters are such that equilibrium incumbents' research
 effort is more elastic than entrants'
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\partial x_{I}^{\star}}{\partial\phi}\frac{\phi}{x_{I}^{\star}}>\frac{\partial x_{e,\omega}^{\star}}{\partial\phi}\frac{\phi}{x_{e,\omega}^{\star}},
\]

\end_inset

an increase in the markup, 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi$
\end_inset

, lowers equilibrium inventors' productivity.
 
\end_layout

